Good histroy of St Stephens Green here - <a href="http://www.ucd.ie/archaeology/documentstore/hc_reports/lod/St_Stephens_Green_Final.pdf" rel="nofollow">www.ucd.ie/archaeology/documentstore/hc_reports/lod/St_St...</a>

It includes LROY 01698  - Showing the fountain and a fancy statue of George II, blown up by the IRA in 1938, and 
LROY 04413 - The note says that the fountains were originally filled to the brim giving the floral centerpiece the appearance of floating. There are other LROY photos shown. [http://www.flickr.com/photos/nlireland] Carol you will be happy to know that all photos are marked &quot;Photos courtesy of the National Library of Ireland&quot;
